{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/pulls/369", "id": 341869824, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzQxODY5ODI0", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/iminuit/pull/369", "diff_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/iminuit/pull/369.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/iminuit/pull/369.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/issues/369", "number": 369, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "adding convenient setting of errordef", "user": {"login": "HDembinski", "id": 2631586, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI2MzE1ODY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2631586?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski", "html_url": "https://github.com/HDembinski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HDembinski/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Adds an easy way to set errordef in units of sigma or as confidence level (cl).\r\n```py\r\n    from iminuit import Minuit\r\n    \r\n    # this is for least-squares; for negative log-likelihood import from iminuit.errordef.nll \r\n    from iminuit.errordef.lsq import sigma, cl\r\n\r\n    def lsq(mu):\r\n        return (mu - 1) ** 2\r\n\r\n    # for standard errors\r\n    m = Minuit(lsq, mu=0, errordef=1 * sigma)\r\n    m.migrad()\r\n    # now m.errors[\"mu\"] is approximately 1\r\n\r\n    # for 2-sigma errors\r\n    m.set_errordef(2 * sigma)  # or sigma * 2\r\n    m.hesse()\r\n    # now m.errors[\"mu\"] is approximately 2\r\n\r\n    # for 99 % confidence level\r\n    m.set_errordef(0.99 * cl)  # or cl * 0.99\r\n    m.hesse()\r\n    # now m.errors[\"mu\"] is approximately 2.6\r\n```", "created_at": "2019-11-17T16:25:03Z", "updated_at": "2020-02-23T20:28:03Z", "closed_at": "2020-02-23T20:27:58Z", "merged_at": "2020-02-23T20:27:58Z", "merge_commit_sha": "b673084bbee06365a6e8c827e9b716a1af0541ef", "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/pulls/369/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/pulls/369/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/issues/369/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/iminuit/statuses/05fc6631778c1710e92016169a39f7043f5a36c9", "head": {"label": "scikit-hep:easy_errordef", "ref": "easy_errordef", "sha": "05fc6631778c1710e92016169a39f7043f5a36c9", "user": {"login": "scikit-hep", "id": 23454624, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjIzNDU0NjI0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23454624?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api